I am trying to create a class structure that involves inheritance and polymorphism. I have a parent class that has a method called "ancestor_feature". I want to create a child class that not only extends the parent class and implements an abstract method, but also needs to override a method from the parent class. How can I achieve this?

```Python
class Ancestor:
  def __init__(self):
